parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
often requiring frequent oil additions
and may exhibit clicking or knocking noises. The engine may stall or shut off without warning
especially when slowing down or coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or shutting off can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
often while driving at low speeds
slowing down
or coming to a stop. The vehicle may restart after coasting to a stop
but the failure can recur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off while in motion, resulting in a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while in motion
the engine and electrical system shut down
the dashboard goes dark
the turn signal does not work
and the steering becomes more difficult.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the transmission feels like it is dropping
the vehicle makes a loud noise
and the "R" or "D" light on the dashboard begins to flash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag and electrical system can cause the airbag light to turn on and off, and the passenger seat belt light to turn on and off, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The airbag light turns on and off
the passenger seat belt light turns on and off
and the dashboard lights and buttons disappear and reappear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the low fuel warning indicator can cause the driver to run out of fuel, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The low fuel warning indicator does not turn on
and the DIC states "Low Fuel Range" but no warning chime or message appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the reverse camera can cause the driver to lose visibility while backing up, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The reverse camera goes black while backing up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heating and Air Conditioning System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the heating and air conditioning system can cause the driver to lose comfort and visibility, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The heating and air conditioning system does not work correctly
the defogger blows cold air
and the air conditioning does not blow cold air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel locks or sticks
the power steering warning light comes on
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel has a delayed response to input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The StabiliTrak or ESC warning light comes on
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel has a delayed response to input
the vehicle's stability is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The binding or sticking of the steering wheel can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel binds or sticks
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel has a delayed response to input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PPS module can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag light is off when the passenger seat is empty
the airbag light is on when someone is in the passenger seat
the fasten seatbelt light flashes and chimes when the passenger seat is empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to fail to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator flashes intermittently
the airbag light comes on
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, including the airbag system, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning light comes on
the vehicle won't start
the dashboard displays a list of "Service Now" indicators
including service airbag
no gauges
speedometer
or radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to engage
the gear shifter feels loose or stuck
the vehicle is unable to shift into park or other gears
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in a particular gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or lurches
the engine RPMs increase or decrease unexpectedly
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift lock release button can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift lock release button fractures or breaks
the vehicle is unable to shift into park or other gears
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stuck ignition key can prevent the vehicle from being turned off or started, leading to safety risks, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle is unable to turn off or start
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accidental shift into manual mode can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in a particular gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift lever is accidentally pushed
the vehicle shifts into manual mode
the engine RPMs increase or decrease unexpectedly
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
